My friend Sheena is form New Dheli, India. She had a bunch of people at her house for and indian curry night, midnight bannana wafles and a serious Jenga tournament. After that we watched some movies and then just went to bed, the next morning we hit the town, she lives in nakatsu and had suhi. I burnt my hand cause I wasn't paying attention while I was serving my tea....
anyway here are some pictues of the night!

Took a 4 day trip to tokyo for a seminar and met up with tomoko to hit the town!!!

So I've been so busy with examns and projects I havnt had time to write anything down here. Well it's been a hell of a month, but all bad things apart there have been really good things like strolling arround the ghettos of oita with some friends. One of those crazy nights include, clubbing in APU's student fav, cool bananas hahaha there is nothing much in oita so everyone who goes out goes there. Then going to some yakiniku in downtown beppu followed by a dipp in onzen and to finish that a strolll in beppu city. That day I went to the sex museum, yeah hyou read right, hahaha apparently beppu is this really sketchy town and they have a sex museum its so weird, with information about animals and other random things. 
Everyone to yakiniku!!! the small plate holds the 3 different sauces for the grilled meat.
Me and some of the excahnge students at cool bananans
me and the norway people!


SEX MUSEUM BEPPU
 really tacky but it's one of beppus atractions!

So I lost my cool posters I had in kyoto when I moved here so I was avvoiding studying for my japanese midterm and I did this hahaha, trying to get a japanese lisence really fucks up your head, I cant sleep nor think properly since all this started hahahaha is reall hell, but the good news is that Im only 2 questions away, at least that was todays score, I got 86% and I need 90% stupid hey? but its japan and I have to work with the system it doesn't matter how silly it is.
Pau aqui esta el video ya bien peusto para que lo puedas ver no se por que no lo habias podido ver, espero que estes muy bien te quiero.

Mama te quiero mucho gracias por todo. This post goes to everyones moms who I know hahaha and have been nice to me, to me grandmothers and to tsuda san, but specially to my mom for being the most wonderfull

Pople it was my birthday and as you know Im in japan and I turned 20 so now finally after a year and a half of illegal drinking im an adult!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!. I was comming back from tokyo feeling shitty cause it was gonna be a weird birthday cause I dont have really close friends right now and all that but it was the other way arround. Paul and Hannah, we take most of our classes together they baked a panckake cake with nutella and jelly all over and put strawberries and bananas on the top and sang happy bdy at 12:00. 
The next day I had yakiniku and got some cool presents including an amazing dream journal. After that I came back to apu and all the people on my floor coocked dinner for me. We started doing tequila shot games but we had to stop drinking in the kitchen so the party moved to my room. My room is tiny but there were like 17 people in there. After a long time and a lot of alchohol we were being erally loud so the security guy came to my room and told us to shut UP. hahahahaha after that ben the australina guy broke my courtains ( no probmel they are fixed now) hahahaha.Anyway later that night we moved the party to aphouse1 and stayed tehre really late. It was a great bda!!!       

I got okonomiyaki birthday cake!

Yesterday was the first official day of uni. I only had a workshop which I thought it was a bit boring cause it was only introductions and things like that. After that I just went to have really spciy curry bit it was good. Today on the other hand was the real first day, I had introduction to economics and Advance Japanese, it went pretty good. Me introduction to economics class is packed there is like 135 people in that class its crazy. The teacher is hilarious, he based his whole lecture on the differences of prodcuing pizzas or robots so most of my notes are full with diagrams of pizzas and robots!!! After that I just came home and chilled out for a bit I have to leave soon cause I have a dorm meeting about some logo for our floor hahahaha kinda lame but still AP HOUSE!
(=  )???

Ok today I got 3 things in my mailbox, 
1.- Phone bill not that excited
2.- letter fromt he scholarship foundation about the seminar in tokyo, pleased.
3.- CARE/BDAY PACKAGE FROM LAURA, THRILLED.
Laura is one of my best friends, we became really good friends in japan, me alvaro and laura were family...
Anyway ever since alvaro and laura left japan has definetly not been the same hahahaha I miss you guys so much. Inside the package were amazing things, like fajitas seasoning, an amazing dotation of Hawaian punch powder!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!. When I was living in the states hawaian punch was my favorite drink, its so goood!!!!!. A photo album with crazy pictures of all our great trips and adventures and MMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMmm gummy bears!!!!!!!!!!!!! YESSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSS as many of you know I have a great weakness for gummy bears once the bag is open I cants stop eating them, hun im really trying not to finish them all at once but who knows what might happen!!!!!! Thanks for the package I really apreciate it

Ok as you might know I moved to a really really small town, on top of that I dont even live in the town I live on top of a mountain so it takes about 15 minutes to go down to beppu. Anyway I still live in a pretty cool enviorement where languages and cultures have no boreder a place where everything and everybody is so international so its pretty good. Since there are a lot of people who were in desperate need of a night out some of the older students took us for a night out in oita, a bigger city next to beppu. We went to a club called COOL BANANAS it was so ghetto aparently this place is kinda clandestine so they dont even pay taxes, anyway its a weird place so small and so cheap hahahaha its like 200 for nomihoudai, people who have been to japan know what that means haahhahahaha. Anyway it was a cool night cause we met up with a lot of the students there. The cool korean and cool thai kids were all there and all the white people as well so it was a pretty good night hahahaha the downside was that we had a bit to muc to drink hahahahaha the place ran out of tequilahahahahha! unbelivable but true.

My last 2 weeks in kyoto were fantastic. Lets start with march 14th, as you know feb.14th is valentines, but in japan march 14th is a holiday as well, its for boys to return presents to the girls so  if i got something in valentines on  march 14ht Im suppoused to give something back to that person (usually chocolates). All the big department stores go crazy arround this time cause all the guys are trying to get presents!.
this is the bottom of Takashimaya dept. store in downtown kyoto where all the sweets stores are.

After like 2 days after white day my friend shinobu who is a photographer asked me if I could model in a kimono for a project she was working on. She is working on the advertisement campaign for a kimono store, so they wanted to shoot some pictures of foreigners in kimono, this day I got a free haircut and got to wear kimono and go arround kyotyo all day plus a free dinner!!!!! good kyoto day

The guy on the left is an italian dude, he is getting married in november this year, the one in the middle is the guy who works in the kimono store he said he allways wears kimono and has more kimonos than jeans!!! (unbelivable) and of course me wiht a weird haircut on the right. Loojk at my amazing shoes (getta) they are made out of snakes skin, COOOOL shoes.
Every night I went back to college residence I pass throu the marvellous Nijo Caslte at night, I finally stopped to get a ghood picture of it, geeze I already miss KYOTO hahahahahaha.

My friends from el coyote made a faiorwel party for me at an izakaya. As japanese costme goes I wasnt allowd to pay for anything that night cause I was leaving and it was a party for me!. Here I am holding a fried frog, the taste wasnt bad but the consistence was a bit weird.

   I got an email from and old friend from mexico that he was coming to japan, so he came with a bunch of people from his university and I gave them a tour of the city, it was a bit of a challenge moving 23 people on public buses bt it was good to see mexicans again it had been a while hahahaha I was beggining to think I was forgetting my spanish. I knew some of the people who ere in the group from high school. It was a good day we went to some cool temples and I got to play tour guide again!.

This was perhaps one of the best fays I've had in kyoto. The scholarship foundation called me at arround 10:23 and woke me up to tell me that they were going to give me the scholarship, for all of those who dont know what an effort it was to send the application and sit the interview it was really unexpected cause they had told me I wasnt going to recieve it, anyway its a long story. After that I called my family and tsuda san which is the same hahaha. After spending the whole morning in pj's watching 24 I went to Ginkakuji to se SAZEN or meditation, I had to seat in a weird position on those pillows for 2 hours and clear my mind ( I couldnt do it, had a lot on my head) I was suppoused to be seating in a 90 degree angle but I couldnt so the priest hit me with his wooden stick, yeah if yuou mess up they hit you and then you have to bow). 
After meditation Tsuda san took me to a GOOOOOOD sushi place, it was so raw but amazingly good and the presentation was impresive.
The picture on the right shows the sushi I ate that night, the flower shapped one was amazingly elaborated, each petal was made from squid, rice and something pink, a real piece of art. The picture on the right shows the sashimi I ate, the red one is maguro or tuna and it was the best tuna sashimi I've ever had, so soft and tastfull.
The lady of the night, tsuda san, who has been more than family to me in this past year and a half.


Finally after so many hours of long basic japanese lessons and everyday exams I graduated the Kyotogaidai international exchange program, graduation was helled at morta memorial hall and after that the exchange studetns went to our building and they gave us or diploma there. Me and carlota were nervous cause they were naming someone from each department to rise and go on stage to recieve the diploma in fron of everyone and we thougt it was gonna be one of us but fortunately a chinese guy did it.
So first picture me and carlote in memorial hall waiting for graduation to start. Then me and the biwako member group hahahaha thats a 5 people member club but the 5th member was  in london, we went to lake biwa during summer and 2 days after graduation we went boat rafting . Me holding my diploma from gaidai and miki looking somehwere else. Piere the other foreigner on the last picture was an exchenge student when I first came to japan, he came to visit for graduatuon, the there is benchan and masaechan hahahaha its weird but guys got more flowers than girls in graduation day, hahaha I didnt get anything...

2nd last fair well party. Carlota left japan on march 23 and that marked the end of the crazy nights out in kyoto. We went to gayagaya in kiamachi to eat and drink a lot for 2 hours. I gave carlota a bottle of sake to remember all tthe fun times in japan. ]


Finally after 20 million fairwell partys I got my own, we just went to old gayagaya in saiin station with people I know. Bunsho was so funny he gave an onzen set since I was moving to beppu and told me to "get in the fucking onzen(hot spring) hahahahaha. Then mike masae and masayuki went as well my graduated friends who stopped being university students and became part of a productive society hahahaha good luck. The kimono team was there as well but only this time I wasnt wearing one, sannennagarane ghahahahaha. And at last the crazy guys from the italian departmen hahahaha ever since laura and alvaro left me and carlota hang out with them they are 1st years and also my age which was weird cause I allways felt older, they gave me a bottle of sake and made everyone signt it. I also got a tshirt from gaya gaya( laura u r so jealous) hahahaha

And just to give a drmaticv touch to kyoto the best picture from kimono day. I cant believe a year and a half has passed, it went so fast, so many people and memories. This was one of the most exciting and amazing experiences ever, I leave behind so many things and people but at the same time take all the memories. To all of those who I met in kyoto and were a part of this thank you it was GREAT.

Before the las italians left we went to have dinner at the sushi place close to my house. I had plans with tsuda to go out to dinner so we just joined with the italian party. I drove tsudas small hona life car and it was fun, Ive been driving ever since, I think im getting used to driving on the other side of the road!!!!!.
  Tsuda san is trying to figure out how to use the electronic menu!!!!

This is a normal ferry restaurant for sushi the sushis are placed on plates that go arround the restaurant.If you want a specific sushi you can order it with the electronic menu on the table.

Hey this post goes to paula, cause I know she has been reading my journal non stop and leaving me messages every day. Its whats keeping me writting this, I know there is at least a couple of persons reading my journal so I guess its better than none hahahahaha anyway pauala thanks for everything and as I promissed here is the pic! take care and to all of u write somehting!"!!!! its late in japan so have a good day in the west. OK this is the best picture I got hahahahah lets take new pictures when Im in mexico ok hahahahaha anyway thanks !

This message goes to my most faithfull reader paula! hahahahahah I feel like only 2 people are reading my journal! Laura and paula hahahaha at least they are the ones leaving my messages anyway Id like to take a moment to say thanks hahahahahah the reason I stopped writing for a while was because I felt no one was really reading it so thanks for reading it now

So people, this is me again updating the journal. Today I went to this huge aquarium in osaka, its kaiyukan, its a great place. Before going to the aquarium me Miki and Hiroki decided to eat okonomiyake in osaka, umeda. Okonomiyaki is like a japanese hot cake but its salty and with sea food and bacon, Its really good, plus they put mayonese and other sauces on top. This was the first the first aquarium where I`ve seen a whale shark. This place is huge its the biggest aquarium in japan and it holds so much water!!!!! by the end of the day I was a bit dizzy cause it was to blue for me anhahahaha and I wanted to go faster but my japanese friends where stopping every 2 steps!!!!!! I was really tired cause I`ve been working a lot lately and this was my day off so I decided to do something good with my time and went there but by the time we were done I was death, I think its the first time in 6 years that I went to bed before 10 and today Im still tired hahahaha I think this job is killing me. THis is me miki and hiroki at the okonomiyaki place, hey guys thanks for coming along! This is me and miki at the entrance of the aquarium. Me and hiroki in front of the huge tank that holds the whale shark. One of the things that impressed me about the aquarium was the seep japanese sea spider crabs!!!! they are huge with long legs like spiders.

As I posted on my last entry everyone is leaving again, its the third time people leave, im glad Im goingt to kyushu soon. I bought a new camera so here are some of the things Ive been doing lately ok as I said I want this to be updated. I went to an isakaya wiht a bunch of people from el coyote, the mexican restaurant I go to every thursday, it was fun. To everyone this is hisashi, he is a good friend here in japan. He speaks english, spanish, italian, freanch, japanese, and chines fluently, talk about smart people! This is me magda and lidia, I decided to make something productive in a beautyful kyoto day so we went to kamo and shimo gamo jinja. Paper cranes, to all of u who are not familiar if u fold a 1000 u get a whish... Everyone, meet koyama san, she is like my supervisor at ABC and she gave me chocolates for valentines! only girls do, and I have to give her white chocolates back next month on the 14th, weird isnt it?

Quick entry, today the dutch left japan, is reallly quiet now at res, only me tsuda the italians and the koreans which means only me and tsuda, here are some pic of the party we just did stupid shit as usuall hahaha and took stupid pictures. Los holandeses se fueron de japon hoy, hiciomos una reunioncita en el cuarto de max, ya no hay nadie mas que yo los koreanos y tsuda y las italienas osea yo y tsuda hahaha bueno aqui estan las fotos

Today I recived a the letter from the scholarship foundation. I got it, im amazing hahahahaha, Im really happy to know that I got the scholarship, From now on its gonna be kanji all along! hahaha im going to be japanese!. I haf baito or part time job at coyote, and it was as allwasy ok, i get free beer hahahaha. My friend yuuta came to my house to celebrate the scholarship thing, so we had a party together, everyone is gone hahaha so it was a lonely party. He is amazing, he brought beer and shuuhai to celebrate todays achievement. Tomorrow Im gonna go to yuutas house to play video games with his brothers! hahahaha it sounds like fun. Im really happy that I got the scholarship cause now I know where Im heading so its really good. My friend laura is gone and I really miss her, I got her turtles hahahaha i hope I dont kill them, by the way my new pets names are Alvaro and Laura, haha in case I get lonele daroo hahahaha. Maureen just joined the party cause she forgot her pursue so she came and got it and now is a three person party yay!!! Thanks to everyone for everything, and all my japan people thanks for makinf this a once in a life time experience!. Me and yuuta with my scholarship presents!!!!!!!!!!!! The two persons party!!! This are my new pets!!!!! the black one is laura and the green one is alvaro hahahaha so I dont forget them !!!! As I said, maureen joined the party hahahaha so it became a three persons party!!!!

Today was evelyns bday and lauara is going back home tomorrow, it sucks, Life wont be the same in japan with out her and alvaro hahahaha yeah stupid cabezon I miss u !!!!. Anyway, I helped laura pack today and god it was a mess hahahaha her room almost exploded and her big lugage was like godzila ne hahaha. It took a while cause I stoped helping and started putting music in my hard drive so Rebecca and laura did everything at the end. After that we went to eat okonomiyaki, or japanese hotcake hahahah yeah japanese hot cake, me rebecca and laura had a lot of food, specially me. After dinner we went to ippai ippai, and yuuta went as well. We drank beer as usuall and ate tons of food yuuta ordered for tony, for once in a change the bill wasnt such a pain in the ass hahaha. Everybody got sad after laura said good bye specially me max and yuuta, we are gonna miss u a lot hon haaha. Unexpected connections we make might not last, yet they stay with us for ever, alvaro and laura thanks for the awesome memories, life in japan wont be the same with out you!!!!!!. Everybody is gone and from tomorroy a new cicle beggins, new people and new experiences, it wont be the same. There is 13 italians comming wtf hahaha I can only handle 3 at a time hahahaha. I went to kameoka for an english lesson today, it was an amazing lesson, 4 old ladies and a old men hahahah they are volunteer guides for the kameoka goverment so they needed to learn english from someone, they did research about mexico and we talked about mexican thing the whole lesson. One of them invited me to kameoka for dinner, tnakatsu yay!!!!!. Note to self hahaha go to kameoka! Laura in her room before packing!!! Me Rebecca and Laura eating okonomiyaki me laura an yuuta at ippai ippai, we got discount because yuuta use to work there

We went down to the river bank in arashiyama for a farewell party for the irish and some of the american kids, hahaha now I really feel everyones is leaving, anyway it was lots of fun, and fireworks, ahhaha, georgy bought some fireworks and we light them up by the river, she was a little dangerous, she burnt my shirt hahahaha, apart from that everything went ok. Masae lost her memory card and I found it yheahhhh, anyway im gonna miss the stupid Irish!!!! This is me with a fire works stick hahahaha, its stop being fun after 5 minutes... This is my friend manuela, she is from Italy and she is going back tomorrow to, Im the godfather of her unborn children!!!!!, be serious manuela... Stupid Irish, im gonna miss u in class, hahahaha leprecunts!!!!!!!, safe trip back home.

This was a fun day, my friend yuuta invited me to his house, I went there for a while and listne to japanese music and his family oprdered pizza for me ahahha i dunno why. When his brother came he was like what a fuck hahahaha a gaijin or a foreigner, he got really surprised to see a foreigner in his house. They have like 5 dogs and they are champions on a lor of things. After this I made rebecca laura and brendan watch white chicks!, ahjhahaha i think is an amazing movie, and laura promised to wathc it before going back home. After that we went to ippai ippai, a local bar with very cheap beer!!!!! hahahahaha 180yen a beer, like 18 pesos, or 1.8 usdl. The night got weird after some many nama mitsu or three beers, and we started to fool arround doing yoga???? hahaha Honey driking with out u wont be the same, dont leave me hahhahaha!!!!! I had hicops and laura was teaching me something to make the go away, or maybe she was just drunk hahahahaha, thanks My friend miki wanted to carry me for some reason hahaha.

My friends taka and mimi invited me to make japanese sweets at one of the local shops. Everyone knows im not really a skillfull person when it comes to crafts so my sweets weren`t that good. Today im gonna go loook for tickets to australia because im flying there in september ti visit PIPA!!!!!!!!. This is what we got to make the candys, we got 2 that were already made and we had to try and make them the same, but as u can see i couldnt do it, hahaha I suck ahhaha. This is my friend taka and me with the sweets, my sweets are really different from the original ones.
Today was victors fair well party, he is going back home tomorrow, sn francisco hahaha everybody is leaving me alone in japan!!!!!

Today was lauras bday party, we had a pre cup or whatever it is in english and then went to the kamogawa, we had a huge party at the river with all of the exchange students. There was a lot of alchol flowing arround for my good friend laura. Then the irish and me and alvaro had t shirts made with lauras face on them and walked all arround the party in purple style hahaha. Everybody got kinda trashed and by the end of the night we came to college residence and yuuta, kyouka and asusa stayed at my place and talked till 6 oclock in the morning in japanese, i have no idea how I managed.

Well i just started this journal cause im sick and I have the time hahaha, well im really really sick i feel im gonna die here, plus japaneses hospitals are really strange, i got a bunch of medicines so I hope I get better, the weather is still shitty and rainy.

Gion matsuri is a festival in japan held in kyoto every year. Its one of japans most famous festivals. It`s original popurpose was to make plagues go away from the city and eventually became a parade. The parade consist on wooden cars or portable jinja that go in a circuit arround the city, and is allways packed. Arround the area of shijo karasuma there are many pf this cars and a lot of food stands and some ohter japanese traditianl food and game stands. This is the time of the year to wear Yukata, the traditional japanese clothes and getta, the wooden shoes. We went to the matsuri downtown and walked through the street all the way to yasaka shrine. The sancturay where the matsuri is held.We met up wit the duthc people and later went to gaya gaya, is one of the izakayas we go to, is a japanese style bar. My friend miki helped me put on my yukata because tying the himo is very hard, so they dressed my up.
